{
    "id": "sysadmin/log-analysis",
    "title": "Inspect System Logs",
    "description": "Use journalctl and tail to extract incident evidence and build a concise report.",
    "image": "/assets/quests/linux_system_log_analysis.jpg",
    "npc": "/assets/npc/orion.jpg",
    "start": "start",
    "dialogue": [
        {
            "id": "start",
            "text": "Services leave breadcrumbs everywhere. We'll transform noisy logs into actionable evidence.",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "triage",
                    "text": "Open the incident playbook"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "triage",
            "text": "First gather a bounded journal extract, then capture a live tail report. Tangible artifacts make handoffs faster during outages.",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "process",
                    "process": "sysadmin-export-journalctl-incident-window",
                    "text": "Export last 200 lines for a service with journalctl"
                },
                {
                    "type": "process",
                    "process": "sysadmin-capture-tail-followup-report",
                    "text": "Tail service logs and compile follow-up notes"
                },
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "quiz-1",
                    "text": "Incident artifacts ready\u2014start log quiz",
                    "requiresItems": [
                        {
                            "id": "8c53ef31-c63c-4f7e-8570-9370d1c0643a",
                            "count": 1
                        },
                        {
                            "id": "2c87205a-5bd9-4c17-91fd-43da70e7021e",
                            "count": 1
                        }
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "quiz-1",
            "text": "Quiz 1/5: Which command shows the newest 200 journal entries for nginx?",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "quiz-2",
                    "text": "journalctl -u nginx -n 200 --no-pager"
                },
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "retry-quiz",
                    "text": "tail -u nginx -n 200"
                },
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "retry-quiz",
                    "text": "journalctl --tail nginx"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "quiz-2",
            "text": "Quiz 2/5: Which command follows new lines as a log file updates?",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "quiz-3",
                    "text": "tail -f /var/log/syslog"
                },
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "retry-quiz",
                    "text": "cat -n /var/log/syslog"
                },
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "retry-quiz",
                    "text": "grep -f /var/log/syslog"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "quiz-3",
            "text": "Quiz 3/5: Why is `--no-pager` useful in scripted incident captures?",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "quiz-4",
                    "text": "It prints directly without interactive paging, so output can be redirected cleanly"
                },
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "retry-quiz",
                    "text": "It hides warnings automatically"
                },
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "retry-quiz",
                    "text": "It compresses logs by default"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "quiz-4",
            "text": "Quiz 4/5: Which pattern is best for a concise incident extract?",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "quiz-5",
                    "text": "Bound time or line count, then annotate key errors"
                },
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "retry-quiz",
                    "text": "Dump all historical logs with no filtering"
                },
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "retry-quiz",
                    "text": "Delete old logs before reading"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "quiz-5",
            "text": "Quiz 5/5: After collecting logs, what should you include in a handoff note?",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "finish",
                    "text": "Timestamp, affected service, observed error pattern, and next action"
                },
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "retry-quiz",
                    "text": "Only the hostname"
                },
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "retry-quiz",
                    "text": "A screenshot with no text context"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "retry-quiz",
            "text": "Almost there. Re-check your journal and tail outputs, then retry.",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "triage",
                    "text": "Retry log triage"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "finish",
            "text": "Outstanding. You can now convert raw logs into evidence the whole ops crew can act on.",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "finish",
                    "text": "Claim log analysis rewards",
                    "requiresItems": [
